name: HEMO_DATA_PHASES
description: This table contains the phases of an invasive procedure performed in a catheterization lab. It is used to group hemodynamic pressure measurements together by phase.

columns.name: FINDING_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier (.1 item) for the finding record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this record.

columns.name: HEMO_PHASES_KEY
columns.description: A unique string to identify the phase.

columns.name: HEMO_PHASE_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores the phase description that the user chose from the preconfigured options, example: resting.

columns.name: USER_ENTERED_PHASE_NAME
columns.description: Stores the phase description that a user typed in instead of choosing from the preconfigured options.

columns.name: PHASE_START_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: The date and time the phase began (UTC).

columns.name: PHASE_END_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: The date and time the phase ended (UTC).
